🔍 What Happened

  You probably tested:
  - ❌ https://api.coditect.ai/ (root path - no handler)
  - ❌ https://api.coditect.ai/health (missing /api/v5 prefix)

  The V5 backend requires /api/v5 prefix on all routes (see backend/src/main.rs:90).

  Expected response from health check:
  {
    "success": true,
    "data": {
      "status": "healthy",
      "service": "coditect-v5-api"
    }
  }

  Try https://api.coditect.ai/api/v5/health now - the ingress routing should be fully propagated by
  this point.

> {
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "service": "coditect-v5-api",
    "status": "healthy"
  }
} 

● 🎉 Perfect! V5 Backend is LIVE!

  The ingress routing is working correctly. You're now hitting the V5 Rust backend through the public
   URL.

  ✅ Confirmed Working

  URL: https://api.coditect.ai/api/v5/health

  Response:
  {
    "success": true,
    "data": {
      "service": "coditect-v5-api",
      "status": "healthy"
    }
  }
